.TH YAML_CREATE 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_create, yaml_create_with_config, yaml_destroy, yaml_reset \- libyaml context lifecycle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "yaml_ctx_t *yaml_create(yaml_role_t " role ");"
.BI "yaml_ctx_t *yaml_create_with_config(yaml_role_t " role ", const yaml_config_t *" config ");"
.BI "void yaml_destroy(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.BI "void yaml_reset(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_create ()
creates a new context with the specified
.I role
(YAML_ROLE_PARSER or YAML_ROLE_SERIALIZER) and default configuration.
.PP
.BR yaml_create_with_config ()
creates a new context with custom configuration.
The
.I config
parameter specifies event queue size, max document size, and strict mode.
.PP
.BR yaml_destroy ()
frees all resources associated with the context.
.PP
.BR yaml_reset ()
resets the context to its initial state, clearing all parsed data and events.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR yaml_create ()
and
.BR yaml_create_with_config ()
return a pointer to the new context, or NULL on failure.
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Each context must be used from a single thread at a time.
Multiple contexts can be used concurrently from different threads.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_feed_input (3),
.BR yaml_next_event (3),
.BR yaml_get_output (3)
